u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||32||2\n|-\n|[[2004\u201305 La Liga|2004\u201305]]\n|8||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||6||1||15||1\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Spain\n!36||2||5||0||0||0||6||1||47||3\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing]]\n|[[2004\u201305 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n|2004\u201305]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Primera Divisi\u00f3n Argentina|Primera Divisi\u00f3n]]\n|17||2||||||||||||||||\n|-\n|[[2005\u201306 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n|2005\u201306]]\n|20||1||||||||||||||||\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!37||3||||||||||||||||\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total\n!513||84||||||||||||||||\n|}\n\n===International===\nSource:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/simeone-intl.html |title=Diego Pablo Simeone \u2013 Century of International Appearances |publisher=Rsssf.com |date=15 June 2002 }}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|colspan=\"3\"|[[Argentina national football team|Argentina national team]]\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|1988||2||1\n|-\n|1989||3||0\n|-\n|1990||1||0\n|-\n|1991||9||2\n|-\n|1992||3||1\n|-\n|1993||13||1\n|-\n|1994||10||0\n|-\n|1995||8||2\n|-\n|1996||6||2\n|-\n|1997||9||1\n|-\n|1998||12||0\n|-\n|1999||11||1\n|-\n|2000||11||0\n|-\n|2001||6||0\n|-\n|2002||2||0\n|-\n!Total||106||11\n|}\n\n====International goals====\n:''Argentina score listed first, score column indicates score after each Simeone goal.''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mundoalbiceleste.com/player/diego-simeone/ |title=Diego Simeone: Argentina International Goals \u2013 Senior Level |publisher=Mundo Albiceleste |access-date=16 August 2018}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! # !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-\n|1.\n|16 July 1988\n|[[Canberra Stadium|Bruce Stadium]], [[Canberra]], Australia\n|{{fb|KSA}}\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|1\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|2\u20130\n|[[Australia Bicentenary Gold Cup]]\n|-\n|2.\n|12 July 1991\n|[[Estadio Ester Roa|Estadio Municipal]], [[Concepci\u00f3n, Chile|Concepci\u00f3n]], Chile\n|{{fb|PAR}}\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|2\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|4\u20131\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[1991 Copa Am\u00e9rica]]\n|-\n|3.\n|21 July 1991\n|[[Estadio Nacional Julio Mart\u00ednez Pr\u00e1danos|Estadio Nacional de Chile]], [[Santiago]], Chile\n|{{fb|COL}}\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|1\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|2\u20131\n|-\n|4.\n|20 October 1992\n|[[King Fahd International Stadium|King Fahd II Stadium]], [[Riyadh]], Saudi Arabia\n|{{fb|KSA}}\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|3\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|3\u20131\n|[[1992 King Fahd Cup Final]]\n|-\n|5.\n|23 June 1993\n|[[Estadio George Capwell]], [[Guayaquil]], Ecuador\n|{{fb|COL}}\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|1\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|1\u20131\n|[[1993 Copa Am\u00e9rica]]\n|-\n|6.{{efn|name=a|The matches against Slovakia League (22 June 1995, Mendoza), in which Simeone scored 1 goal, and against Poland B League (20 June 1996, Tucum\u00e1n), in which Simeone also scored 1 goal, were originally considered full international matches by the Argentine FA, but later removed from the list of official matches.}}\n|22 June 1995\n|[[Estadio Malvinas Argentinas]], [[Mendoza, Argentina|Mendoza]], Argentina\n|{{fb|SVK}} League\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|5\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|6\u20130<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.11v11.com/matches/argentina-v-slovakia-22-june-1995-245862/ |title=Argentina VS Slovakia, 22 June 1995 |access-date=16 August 2018}}</ref>\n|[[Exhibition game#International football|Friendly]]\n|-\n|7.\n|11 July 1995\n|[[Estadio Parque Artigas]], [[Paysand\u00fa]], Uruguay\n|{{fb|CHI}}\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|2\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|4\u20130\n|[[1995 Copa Am\u00e9rica]]\n|-\n|8.{{efn|name=a}}\n|20 June 1996\n|[[Tucum\u00e1n, Tucum\u00e1n|Tucum\u00e1n]], Argentina\n|{{fb|Poland}} B League\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|\u2013\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|2\u20130\n|Copa La Gaceta\n|-\n|9.\n|9 October 1996\n|[[Estadio Polideportivo de Pueblo Nuevo|Polideportivo de Pueblo Nuevo]], [[San Crist\u00f3bal, T\u00e1chira|San Crist\u00f3bal]], Venezuela\n|{{fb|VEN}}\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|3\u20131\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|5\u20132\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[1998 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|1998 FIFA World Cup qualification]]\n|-\n|10.\n|8 June 1997\n|[[Estadio Monumental Antonio Vespucio Liberti|El Monumental]], [[Buenos Aires]], Argentina\n|rowspan=\"2\"|{{fb|ECU}}\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|2\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|2\u20130\n|-\n|11.\n|1 July 1999\n|[[Estadio Feliciano C\u00e1ceres]], [[Luque]], Paraguay\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|1\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:center\"|3\u20131\n|[[1999 Copa Am\u00e9rica Group C|1999 Copa Am\u00e9rica]]\n|}\n{{notelist}}\n\n===Managerial===\n{{updated|match played 11 March 2020}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|+ Managerial record by team and tenure\t\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Team\n!rowspan=\"2\"|From\n!rowspan=\"2\"|To\n!colspan=5|Record\n!rowspan=\"2\"|{{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n!{{Tooltip|G|Games managed}}\n!{{Tooltip|W|Games won}}\n!{{Tooltip|D|Games drawn}}\n!{{Tooltip|L|Games lost}}\n!{{Tooltip|Win %|Winning percentage}}\n|-\n|[[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing Club]]\n|18 February 2006\n|4 May 2006\n{{WDL|14|5|3|6}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Estudiantes de La Plata|Estudiantes La Plata]]\n|18 May 2006\n|3 December 2007\n{{WDL|60|34|15|11}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Club Atl\u00e9tico River Plate|River Plate]]\n|15 December 2007\n|7 November 2008\n{{WDL|45|20|13|12}}\n|\n|-\n|[[San Lorenzo de Almagro|San Lorenzo]]\n|15 April 2009\n|3 April 2010\n{{WDL|50|22|9|19}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Calcio Catania|Catania]]\n|19 January 2011\n|1 June 2011\n{{WDL|18|7|3|8}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bdfutbol.com/en/p/l581.html?temp=2010-11|title=Simeone: Diego Pablo Simeone Gonz\u00e1lez: Matches 2010\u201311|publisher=BDFutbol|accessdate=16 January 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing Club]]\n|21 June 2011\n|23 December 2011\n{{WDL|20|8|10|2}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]]\n|23 December 2011\n|''Present''\n{{WDL|467|280|109|78}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bdfutbol.com/en/p/l581.html?temp=2011-12|title=Simeone: Diego Pablo Simeone Gonz\u00e1lez: Matches 2011\u201312|publisher=BDFutbol|accessdate=16 January 2019}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.bdfutbol.com/en/p/l581.html?temp=2012-13|title=Simeone: Diego Pablo Simeone Gonz\u00e1lez: Matches 2012\u201313|publisher=BDFutbol|accessdate=16 January 2019}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.bdfutbol.com/en/p/l581.html?temp=2013-14|title=Simeone: Diego Pablo Simeone Gonz\u00e1lez: Matches 2013\u201314|publisher=BDFutbol|accessdate=16 January 2019}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.bdfutbol.com/en/p/l581.html?temp=2014-15|title=Simeone: Diego Pablo Simeone Gonz\u00e1lez: Matches 2014\u201315|publisher=BDFutbol|accessdate=16 January 2019}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.bdfutbol.com/en/p/l581.html?temp=2015-16|title=Simeone: Diego Pablo Simeone Gonz\u00e1lez: Matches 2015\u201316|publisher=BDFutbol|accessdate=16 January 2019}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.bdfutbol.com/en/p/l581.html?temp=2016-17|title=Simeone: Diego Pablo Simeone Gonz\u00e1lez: Matches 2016\u201317|publisher=BDFutbol|accessdate=16 January 2019}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.bdfutbol.com/en/p/l581.html?temp=2017-18|title=Simeone: Diego Pablo Simeone Gonz\u00e1lez: Matches 2017\u201318|publisher=BDFutbol|accessdate=16 January 2019}}<br>{{cite web|url=https://www.bdfutbol.com/en/p/l581.html?temp=2018-19|title=Simeone: Diego Pablo Simeone Gonz\u00e1lez: Matches 2018\u201319|publisher=BDFutbol|accessdate=16 January 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Total\n{{WDLtot|674|376|162|136}}\n!\u2014\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n===Player===\n'''Atl\u00e9tico Madrid'''\n*[[La Liga]]: [[1995\u201396 La Liga|1995\u201396]]\n*[[Copa del Rey]]: [[1995\u201396 Copa del Rey|1995\u201396]]\n\n'''Inter Milan'''\n*[[UEFA Cup]]: [[1997\u201398 UEFA Cup|1997\u201398]]\n\n'''Lazio'''\n*[[Serie A]]: [[1999\u20132000 Serie A|1999\u20132000]]\n*[[Coppa Italia]]: [[1999\u20132000 Coppa Italia|1999\u20132000]]\n*[[Supercoppa Italiana]]: [[2000 Supercoppa Italiana|2000]]\n*[[UEFA Super Cup]]: [[1999 UEFA Super Cup|1999]]\n\n'''Argentina'''\n*[[Copa Am\u00e9rica]]: [[1991 Copa Am\u00e9rica|1991]], [[1993 Copa Am\u00e9rica|1993]] \n*[[King Fahd Cup]]: [[1992 King Fahd Cup|1992]]\n*[[Football at the Summer Olympics|Olympic Silver Medal]]: [[Football at the 1996 Summer Olympics \u2013 Men's tournament|1996]]\n\n'''Individual'''\n*[[Trofeo EFE]]: 1995\u201396\n\n===Manager===\n'''Estudiantes La Plata'''\n*[[Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n]]: [[2006\u201307 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n#Torneo Apertura|2006 Torneo Apertura]]\n\n'''River Plate'''\n*Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n: [[2007\u201308 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n#Torneo Clausura|2008 Torneo Clausura]]\n\n'''Atl\u00e9tico Madrid'''\n*La Liga: [[2013\u201314 La Liga|2013\u201314]]\n*Copa del Rey: [[2012\u201313 Copa del Rey|2012\u201313]]\n*[[Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a]]: [[2014 Supercopa de Espa\u00f1a|2014]]\n*[[UEFA Champions League]]: runner-up: [[2013\u201314 UEFA Champions League|2013\u201314]], [[2015\u201316 UEFA Champions League|2015\u201316]]\n*[[UEFA Europa League]]: [[2011\u201312 UEFA Europa League|2011\u201312]], [[2017\u201318 UEFA Europa League|2017\u201318]]\n*[[UEFA Super Cup]]: [[2012 UEFA Super Cup|2012]], [[2018 UEFA Super Cup|2018]]\n\n'''Individual'''\n*[[European Coach of the Season (association football)|European Coach of the Season]]: 2011\u201312\n*[[La Liga Manager of the Month]]: October 2013, November 2015, March 2017\n*[[LFP Awards|La Liga Coach of the Year]]: [[LFP Awards|2012\u201313]], [[LFP Awards|2013\u201314]], [[LFP Awards|2015\u201316]]\n*[[Miguel Mu\u00f1oz Trophy]]: [[2013\u201314 La Liga|2013\u201314]], [[2015\u201316 La Liga|2015\u201316]]\n*[[Facebook Football Awards|Facebook/MARCA Football Awards (Best Manager)]]: 2016<ref>http://www.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/2016/05/12/5734e085ca47411c328b46b5.html</ref>\n*[[IFFHS World's Best Club Coach]]: [[IFFHS|2016]]\n*[[Globe Soccer Awards|Globe Soccer Master Coach Special Award]]: 2017<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.globesoccer.com/winners/diego-pablo-simeone-master-coach-special-award/|title=Diego Pablo Simeone MASTER COACH SPECIAL AWARD 2017|website=Dubai Globe Soccer Awards}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of footballers with 100 or more caps]]\n*[[List of UEFA Cup and Europa League winning managers]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*{{BDFutbol}}\n*{{BDFutbol manager|581}}\n*[http://it.sports.yahoo.com/fo/profiles/4247.html Profile and Statistics at yahoo.com]{{dead link|date=September 2017|bot=InternetArchiveBot|fix-attempted=yes }}\n*{{NFT player}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20090224012956/http://www.futbolxxi.com/Tecnico.aspx?ID=362&SEOTecnico=Simeone+Diego+Pablo Managerial statistics in the Argentine Primera] at F\u00fatbol XXI {{in lang|es}} \n*{{Cite web|url=http://futbolfactory.futbolweb.net/index.php?ff=historicos&f2=00001&idjugador=362|title=Futbol Factory profile|access-date=21 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071020025307/http://futbolfactory.futbolweb.net/index.php?ff=historicos&f2=00001&idjugador=362|archive-date=20 October 2007|url-status=dead|language=es}}\n*[http://atleticomadrid.ru/coach.html Profile Simeone] {{in lang|ru}}\n\n{{Atl\u00e9tico Madrid squad}}\n{{La Liga managers}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Awards\n| bg = Gold\n| fg = Black\n| bordercolor = Black\n| list1 = \n{{UEFA Europa League winning managers}}\n{{Trofeo EFE}}\n{{2013\u201314 La Liga Team of the Year}}\n{{La Liga Coach of the Year (LFP)}}\n{{Miguel Mu\u00f1oz Trophy}}\n{{IFFHS World's Best Club Coach}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Argentina squads\n| bg = #6AB5FF\n| fg = white\n| bordercolor = #00355E\n| list1 = \n{{Argentina squad 1991 Copa Am\u00e9rica}}\n{{Argentina squad 1992 King Fahd Cup}}\n{{Argentina squad 1993 Copa Am\u00e9rica}}\n{{Argentina squad 1994 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Argentina squad 1995 Copa Am\u00e9rica}}\n{{Argentina men's football squad 1996 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Argentina squad 1998 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Argentina squad 1999 Copa Am\u00e9rica}}\n{{Argentina squad 2002 FIFA World Cup}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Managerial positions\n| list1 = \n{{Racing Club managers}}\n{{Estudiantes de La Plata managers}}\n{{River Plate managers}}\n{{San Lorenzo de Almagro managers}}\n{{Atl\u00e9tico Madrid managers}}\n}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Simeone, Diego}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Simeone family]]\n[[Category:Argentine people of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Buenos Aires]]\n[[Category:Argentine footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Club Atl\u00e9tico V\u00e9lez Sarsfield footballers]]\n[[Category:A.C. Pisa 1909 players]]\n[[Category:Sevilla FC players]]\n[[Category:Atl\u00e9tico Madrid footballers]]\n[[Category:Inter Milan players]]\n[[Category:S.S. Lazio players]]\n[[Category:Racing Club de Avellaneda footballers]]\n[[Category:Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Serie A players]]\n[[Category:Serie B players]]\n[[Category:La Liga players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Cup winning players]]\n[[Category:Argentina youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Argentina under-20 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Argentina international footballers]]\n[[Category:1991 Copa Am\u00e9rica players]]\n[[Category:1992 King Fahd Cup players]]\n[[Category:1993 Copa Am\u00e9rica players]]\n[[Category:1994 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:1995 Copa Am\u00e9rica players]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 1996 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:1998 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:1999 Copa Am\u00e9rica players]]\n[[Category:2002 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:Copa Am\u00e9rica-winning players]]\n[[Category:FIFA Confederations Cup-winning players]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in football]]\n[[Category:Olympic footballers of Argentina]]\n[[Category:Olympic silver medalists for Argentina]]\n[[Category:FIFA Century Club]]\n[[Category:Argentine expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Argentine expatriate sportspeople in Italy]]\n[[Category:Argentine expatriate sportspeople in Spain]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Italy]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Spain]]\n[[Category:Argentine football managers]]\n[[Category:Racing Club de Avellaneda managers]]\n[[Category:Estudiantes de La Plata managers]]\n[[Category:River Plate managers]]\n[[Category:San Lorenzo managers]]\n[[Category:Calcio Catania managers]]\n[[Category:Atl\u00e9tico Madrid managers]]\n[[Category:Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n managers]]\n[[Category:Serie A managers]]\n[[Category:La Liga managers]]\n[[Category:UEFA Europa League winning managers]]\n[[Category:Argentine expatriate football managers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate football managers in Italy]]\n[[Category:Expatriate football managers in Spain]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Argentinian football coach and former player}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Spanish name|Simeone|Gonz\u00e1lez}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Diego Simeone\n| image          = Diego Pablo Simeone en la presentaci\u00f3n de la promoci\u00f3n de la estaci\u00f3n Estadio Metropolitano.jpg\n| image_size     = 220\n| caption        = Simeone during an [[Atl\u00e9tico Madrid]] meeting in September 2017\n| fullname       = Diego Pablo Simeone Gonz\u00e1lez<ref>{{cite web |url=http://actas.rfef.es/actas/RFEF_CmpActa1?cod_primaria=1000144&CodActa=57319 |title=Acta del Partido celebrado el 18 de mayo de 2019, en Valencia |trans-title=Minutes of the Match held on 18 May 2019, in Valencia |publisher=Royal Spanish Football Federation |accessdate=3 July 2019 |language=Spanish}}</ref>\n| birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1970|4|28|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Buenos Aires]], Argentina\n| height       