s to Success |date=2005 |publisher=Human Kinetics |isbn=9780736054355 |page=vi |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qFCWeBzQQmcC&pg=PR6}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{dts|2006|June|9|format=dmy}} to {{dts|2006|July|9|format=dmy}}\n| [[2006 FIFA World Cup|Germany 2006 FIFA World Cup]]\n| 3\n| <ref>{{cite web |title=Infographic: Billions of Dollars for Billions of Viewers |url=https://www.statista.com/chart/14357/tv-rights-revenue-of-fifa/ |website=[[Statista|Statista Infographics]] |date=21 June 2018 |accessdate=16 August 2018}}</ref><ref>Tom Dunmore, [https://books.google.com/books?id=9j1wbp2t1usC&pg=PA235#v=onepage&q&f=false Historical Dictionary of Soccer], page 235, quote \"The World Cup is now the most-watched sporting event in the world on television, above even the Olympic Games.\"</ref>\n|-\n| {{dts|2019|May|30|format=dmy}} to {{dts|2019|July|14|format=dmy}}\n| [[2019 Cricket World Cup|2019 ICC Cricket World Cup (England & Wales)]]\n| 2.6\n| <ref>{{cite web |title=CWC 2019 shatters audience records |url=https://www.sport24.co.za/Cricket/CricketWorldCup2019/cwc-2019-shatters-audience-records-20190712 |website=sport24 |publisher=sport24 |accessdate=14 July 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Armstrong |first1=Jeremy |title=One billion watch cricket's biggest rivals India and Pakinstan at Old Trafford |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/cricket/one-billion-watch-crickets-biggest-16528033 |accessdate=27 June 2019 |work=[[Daily Mirror]] |date=16 June 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"india=pakistan\"/>\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Cricket]]\n|-\n| {{dts|2015|February|14|format=dmy}} to {{dts|2015|March|29|format=dmy}}\n| [[2015 Cricket World Cup|2015 ICC Cricket World Cup (Australia & New Zealand)]]\n| 2.2\n| <ref name=\"Kumar\">{{cite news |last=Kumar |first=Abhishek |title=FIFA World Cup 2018: Find Out How Much Prize Money Winners France Have Received (in Rupees) |url=http://www.india.com/fifa-world-cup-2018/breakdown-of-fifa-world-cup-2018-prize-money-awarded-at-each-stage-in-rupees-cricket