ld.html |title=Gold medal game huge TV hit on both sides |publisher=CBC |date= 2010-03-01 |accessdate=2011-11-01}}</ref> According to multiple sources, 13.3 million Canadians watched [[2010 Winter Olympics opening ceremony|the games' opening ceremony]], which was the previous record.<ref>{{cite news|last=Grohmann |first=Karolos |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSTRE61C2GL20100213 |title=Games opening ceremony is most watched TV event in Canada |work=Reuters |date= 13 February 2010|accessdate=2011-05-04}}</ref>\n\nMany believed the final game of the [[1972 Summit Series]] had up to 18 million viewers, but only 4.3 million TVs tuned in. This statistic does not represent the reality that most school children (representing the tail end of the baby-boom i.e. a large population) nationwide watched the game in gymnasiums on only one or two TVs. 10.3 million people watched the ice hockey gold medal final of the 2002 Winter Olympics.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newswire.ca/en/releases/archive/March2010/12/c9483.html |title=2010 Gold Medal Game Is the Apex of TV Viewing in Canada as Legend of '72 Summit Series Finally Laid to Rest |publisher=Newswire.ca |date= March 2010|accessdate=2011-05-04}}</ref>\n\n===China===\n[[China Central Television]]'s [[CCTV New Year's Gala|Spring Festival Gala]] has regularly attracted between 700 million<ref>{{cite news|url=http://travel.cnn.com/7-ways-celebrate-chinese-new-year-395376|title=7 ways to celebrate Chinese New Year|publisher=CNN|date=8 February 2013|quote=It's also probably the biggest show on the planet, attracting 700 million viewers, six times the Super Bowl's audience.}}</ref> to 1.17 billion viewers annually.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/I4FMzYzQjutyUNOQ_M8eFg|title=A record 1.17 billion viewers struggled through the 2019 Gala|publisher=[[Shanghaiist]]|date=8 January 2019|quote=According to the China Media Group, there were a whopping 1.17 billion masochists who tuned in for the gala on Monday night, watching on TV, through apps, and online. That\u2019s about 42 million more viewers than last year.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sony.com/SCA/company-news/press-releases/sony-columbia-records/2013/pop-star-celine-dion-set-to-sing-at-the-2013-cctv-.shtml|title=Pop Star Celine Dion Set to Sing at the 2013 CCTV Spring Festival Gala|publisher=[[Sony]]|date=30 January 2013|quote=The gala has made some world records: It has the world's highest audience numbers of its kind, reaching more than one billion (1,000,000,000.) viewers.}}</ref>\n\nThe CCTV's main evening news broadcast [[Xinwen Lianbo]] has a daily audience of around 135 million people,<ref name=mag>{{cite web|url=http://www.thatsmags.com/shanghai/articles/11211|title=TV in the PRC|publisher=[[that's Shanghai]]|date=5 December 2012|quote=With an estimated daily audience of around 135 million\u2013 14 times the audience of the highest-rated US news show \u2013 CCTV's Xinwen Lianbo is one of the world's most-watched programs. Such is its power that last month the 2013 advertising slots were sold for a record RMB5.4 billion, with Wuliangye, Maotai and Gome spending over RMB1 billion between them on the five-second countdown before the show begins.}}</ref> and it is also one of the most expensive shows in the world per advertising spots, with its 2013 advertising slots selling for a record of 5.4 billion yuan.<ref name=mag/>\n\n===France===\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n|-\n!Rank !! Show !! Episode !! Number of viewers !! Date !! Network\n|-\n| align=\"center\"|1 || [[1998 FIFA World Cup]] || [[1998 FIFA World Cup Final|Brazil vs France]] (final) || 23,647,000 || {{dts|format=dmy|1998|July|12}} || [[TF1]], [[Canal+]]\n|-\n| align=\"center\"|2 || [[UEFA Euro 2016]] || [[UEFA Euro 2016 Final|Portugal vs France]] (final) || 22,292,000 || {{dts|format=dmy|2016|July|10}} || [[M6 (TV channel)|M6]], [[BeIN Sports (France)|BeIN Sports]]\n|-\n| align=\"center\"|3 || [[2006 FIFA World Cup]] || [[2006 FIFA World Cup 